Varil shares his proposal planning story for Krisha with us: "I wanted the moment to be nothing short of magical—something intimate, meaningful, and completely 'us.' After some searching, I stumbled upon the picturesque town of Sant Elm in Mallorca, Spain. It was like a hidden gem waiting to be discovered. With its serene charm, sweeping ocean views, and that perfect hush of tranquility, it instantly felt right. Everything about it—the simplicity, the scenery, the stillness—echoed what we love most. I knew then, this was the place where I’d ask her the biggest question of our lives." 

Share your proposal story with us at editor@weddingsutra.com or tag us with #ProposalXWeddingSutra

latestPosts.caption:
Ishmita shares her proposal story with us: “Anmol and I met two years ago as strangers. We were from two different states, with completely different cultures and work profiles. I was serving the nation as a government officer, far removed from the glitz and glamour, while Anmol was living a fast-paced, glittering corporate life. It wasn’t love at first sight—but yes, it was definitely a feeling at first sight. A year later, we met again, and this time, everything felt different. It was as if both of us just knew—there was something special about this bond.nBut even before any proposal, both our hearts were hesitant. Coming from such different backgrounds and imagining a future together wasn’t easy for either of us. But as they say, when something is written in the stars, no human can change it. And now, after two whole years, Anmol has officially proposed to me. Maybe the answer had always been a yes—it was just a matter of him asking. And with this proposal, we’re finally about to begin our forever.”

Share your proposal story with us at editor@weddingsutra.com or tag us with #ProposalXWeddingSutra

Couple: @ish_smita, @anmol30896
Venue: Glennville Forest Resort and Spa
Photos Courtesy: @studio_pranjuphotophy
